
<REFENTRY id="passwd">
<REFMETA><REFENTRYTITLE>passwd</REFENTRYTITLE></REFMETA>

<REFNAMEDIV>
<REFNAME>passwd</REFNAME>

<REFPURPOSE>
change user password
</REFPURPOSE>

</REFNAMEDIV>

<REFSYNOPSISDIV>
<SYNOPSIS>
passwd [-g] [-r|R] group
passwd [-x max] [-n min] [-w warn] [-i inact] name
passwd {-l|-u} name
</SYNOPSIS>
</REFSYNOPSISDIV>

<REFSECT1>
<TITLE>Description</TITLE>
<PARA>
<COMMAND>passwd</COMMAND> changes passwords for user and group accounts. 
A normal user may only change the password for their own account, the 
super user may change the password for any account.  The administrator 
of a group may change the password for the group. <COMMAND>passwd</COMMAND> 
also changes password expiry dates and intervals.
</PARA>
</REFSECT1>

<REFSECT1>
<title>Options</title>
<variablelist>

<varlistentry>
<term>-g</term>
<listitem>
<para>
changes the password for the named group.
</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>-r</term>
<listitem>
<para>
combines with -g to remove the current password from the named group.
</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>-R</term>
<listitem>
<para>
combines with -g to restrict the named group for all users.
</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>-x max</term>
<listitem>
<para>
sets the maximum number of days a password remains valid.
</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>-n min</term>
<listitem>
<para>
sets the minimum number of days before a password may be changed.
</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>-w warn</term>
<listitem>
<para>
sets the number of days warning the user will receive before
their password will expire.
</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>-i inactive</term>
<listitem>
<para>
disables an account after the password has been expired for the given
number of days.
</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>-l</term>
<listitem>
<para>
disables an account by changing the password to a value which
matches no possible encrypted value.
</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term>-u</term>
<listitem>
<para>
re-enables an account by changing the password back to its previous value.
</para>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

</variablelist>
</REFSECT1>

</REFENTRY>
